b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15088.htm)  [Next](sbe15090.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 194\n\n### ELEVENTH BR\xc3\x82HMA _N_ A.\n\nThis is indeed the highest penance, if a man, laid up with sickness, suffers\npain 1. He who knows this, conquers the highest world.\n\nThis is indeed the highest penance, if they carry a dead person into the\nforest 2. He who knows this, conquers the highest world.\n\nThis is indeed the highest penance, if they place a dead person on the fire 3.\nHe who knows this, conquers the highest world.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[194:1](sbe15089.htm#fr_566) The meaning is that, while he is suffering pain\nfrom illness, he should think that he was performing penance. If he does that,\nhe obtains the same reward for his sickness which he would have obtained for\nsimilar pain inflicted on himself for the sake of performing penance.\n\n[194:2](sbe15089.htm#fr_567) This is like the penance of leaving the village\nand living in the forest.\n\n[194:3](sbe15089.htm#fr_568) This is like the penance of entering into the\nfire.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: V, 12](sbe15090.htm)\n\n'